This paper deals with relation extraction and database population using machine learning models, which are common topics in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) research. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of pre-existing structured databases, which falls under the scope of database systems (cs.DB). The machine learning models used in the paper are based on matrix factorization, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research.
